cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper is about evolutionary algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence and optimization. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses self-adjusting population sizing mechanisms, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI another likely sub-category. Theoretical studies and computer simulations are used to support the claims made in the paper, indicating that it could also fit under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the role of population sizing in evolutionary algorithms, which is relevant to software engineering, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) a possible sub-category as well.
